    Stack --> argcBox[argc = 4]
    Stack --> argvBox[argv Array of Pointers]
    argvBox --> p0[argv 0 = ./prog]
    argvBox --> p1[argv 1 = 25]
    argvBox --> p2[argv 2 = Hello]
    argvBox --> p3[argv 3 = 3.14]
    argvBox --> pN[argv 4 = NULL terminator]
    p0 --> str0[String ./prog]
    p1 --> str1[String 25]
    p2 --> str2[String Hello]
    p3 --> str3[String 3.14]
```

**Reading the diagram:**
- The shell creates the strings in read-only memory.
- `argv` is an array of 4 pointers (plus a `NULL` sentinel at `argv[4]`).
- `argc` is a separate integer variable.

