## 4.2 Structure Memory Layout — `struct Student`

For `struct Student { int rollNo; char name[30]; float marks; }`, a typical (simplified, no padding) memory map is:

```mermaid
graph TB
    subgraph ST[Structure Variable s1 in Memory]
        A[Offset 0: rollNo - 4 bytes]
        B[Offset 4: name 0 - 1 byte]
        C[Offset 5: name 1 - 1 byte]
        D[Offset 33: name 29 - 1 byte]
        E[Offset 34: marks - 4 bytes]
    end
    A -->|int| B
    B -->|char array| D
    D -->|float| E
```

**Key takeaway:** Members are stored **sequentially** within a structure. The total size is at least the sum of all member sizes (often slightly more due to padding).

