## 4.3 Block-Level Flow — Array of Structures with Functions

```mermaid
graph TD
    Start([main starts]) --> Declare[Declare struct Student class MAX]
    Declare --> ReadN[Read n from user]
    ReadN --> CallRead[Call readStudents class n]
    CallRead --> LoopRead[Loop i = 0 to n-1: scanf into class i members]
    LoopRead --> Compute[Loop: class i total = m1 + m2 + m3]
    Compute --> CallDisp[Call displayStudents class n]
    CallDisp --> LoopDisp[Loop i = 0 to n-1: print class i members]
    LoopDisp --> End([main returns 0])
```

**Engineering utility:** This is the canonical flow for any CRUD (Create-Read-Update-Delete) record-management program in C.

