## 4.4 Pass-by-Value vs Pass-by-Address — Visual Comparison

```mermaid
graph TB
    subgraph V[Pass by VALUE]
        V1[Original struct in main] -->|copied| V2[Local copy in function]
        V2 -->|modifications| V3[Local copy changed]
        V1 -->|unchanged| V4[Original remains same]
    end

    subgraph A[Pass by ADDRESS]
        A1[Original struct in main] -->|address &amp passed| A2[Pointer p in function]
        A2 -->|p->x modifies original| A3[Original struct changed]
    end
```

**Rule of thumb:** Use pass-by-value when you want to **protect** the data; use pass-by-address when you want to **modify** the data or when the structure is large (to avoid copy overhead).

