### Question A (14 Marks) — MAIN

**`[KTU University Exam - Dec 2024]`**

**(a) [7 marks]** Write a C program to accept **three integers** as command-line arguments and print their sum, product, and average. Handle the case where the user does not provide exactly three arguments.

**(b) [7 marks]** Define a structure `Complex` with members `real` and `imag` (both `float`). Write a C program that:
   (i) Reads two complex numbers from the user.
   (ii) Uses a function `addComplex` to compute their sum and return the result.
   (iii) Displays the result in the form `a + bi`.

