#### Model Solution for (a) — 7 marks

```c
#include <stdio.h>
#include <stdlib.h>

int main(int argc, char *argv[])
{
    int a, b, c, sum, product;
    float average;

    if (argc != 4) {
        printf("Usage: %s <num1> <num2> <num3>\n", argv[0]);
        return 1;
    }

    a = atoi(argv[1]);
    b = atoi(argv[2]);
    c = atoi(argv[3]);

    sum      = a + b + c;
    product  = a * b * c;
    average  = sum / 3.0f;   // Note: 3.0 to avoid integer division

    printf("Sum      = %d\n",   sum);
    printf("Product  = %d\n",   product);
    printf("Average  = %.2f\n", average);

    return 0;
}
```

**Execution:**

```bash
./a.out 4 5 6
Sum      = 15
Product  = 120
Average  = 5.00
```

**Mark split (7 marks):**
- Correct signature and argument validation — **2 marks**.
- Correct use of `atoi` for conversions — **2 marks**.
- Correct computation of sum, product, and float average — **2 marks**.
- Proper formatted output — **1 mark**.

