#### Model Solution for (b) — 7 marks

```c
#include <stdio.h>

struct Complex {
    float real;
    float imag;
};

// Function returning a structure
struct Complex addComplex(struct Complex n1, struct Complex n2)
{
    struct Complex result;
    result.real = n1.real + n2.real;
    result.imag = n1.imag + n2.imag;
    return result;
}

int main(void)
{
    struct Complex c1, c2, sum;

    printf("Enter first complex number (real imag): ");
    scanf("%f %f", &c1.real, &c1.imag);

    printf("Enter second complex number (real imag): ");
    scanf("%f %f", &c2.real, &c2.imag);

    sum = addComplex(c1, c2);

    printf("\nFirst  Number : %.2f + %.2fi\n", c1.real, c1.imag);
    printf("Second Number : %.2f + %.2fi\n", c2.real, c2.imag);
    printf("Sum           : %.2f + %.2fi\n", sum.real, sum.imag);

    return 0;
}
```

**Sample Run:**

```
Enter first complex number (real imag): 3 4
Enter second complex number (real imag): 5 6

First  Number : 3.00 + 4.00i
Second Number : 5.00 + 6.00i
Sum           : 8.00 + 10.00i
```

**Mark split (7 marks):**
- Correct structure definition — **1 mark**.
- Correct function signature and return type — **2 marks**.
- Correct member-wise addition — **2 marks**.
- Correct reading, calling, and displaying with proper format — **2 marks**.

